p=\frac{1}{n}
n,p
 P(M=0)=\bigg(1-\frac{1}{n}\bigg) \cdot \bigg(1-\frac{1}{n} \bigg)\ldots \bigg(1-\frac{1}{n} \bigg) \approx e^{-1} 
 P(M=1)=\frac{1}{n} \bigg(1-\frac{1}{n} \bigg)^{n-1}+\frac{1}{n} \bigg(1-\frac{1}{n} \bigg)^{n-1}+ \ldots+\frac{1}{n} \bigg(1-\frac{1}{n} \bigg)^{n-1}=\binom{n}{1} \frac{1}{n}\bigg(1-\frac{1}{n} \bigg)^{n-1} 
 \mathbf{E}M=\sum_{k=0}^{n}k\binom{n}{k}p^{k}(1-p)^{n-k} 
 \mathbf{E}M=np=1 
